<br>
3 Summoned flowing thought / clarity items with resists and ac  on them<br>
<br>
4 A port line for all casting classes wis and int pure casters only.<br>
<br>
5 A pet that actually deserves half the xp due to the damage<br>
output it has .<br>
<br>
6 The ability to improve travel speed of our pets but not ourselves is perhaps the height of irony in our spell lines<br>
<br>
7 Pets that come equipped in one cast able to battle high end<br>
mobs / dragonbane pets/ 59+ mobs multipurpose mob pets<br>
<br>
8 The ability to use our shield line/regen armor/burnout lines<br>
on others <br>
<br>
9 The ability to equip and use all our summoned items and perhaps an adv skill set so we can use the weapons and armor<br>
effectively  against all mobs in pet restricted zones<br>
<br>
10 Useful summoned weaponry level restricted of course but<br>
on par with melee/missle weapons commonly carried by those<br>
levels with full inclusion of twinking which aint that hard these days.<br>
<br>
11 Master of the Elements ? should be able to defend himself<br>
with a resist line of SPELLS  not items that take up slots badly<br>
needed for int ac hp mana etc ad infinitum <br>
<br>
12 When 6 mages with pets can kill the same mobs as 6 wizzies can then we will be fun to play <br>
<br>
these are only my thots on some things as a mage <br>
