<br>
<br>
1.  No way VI will give us focus + resist items to summon.  We have some summoned resists items (it would be nice to get more), and we have summoned focus items.  One of the ways VI will make the dropped focus items better than summoned is to include other stats on them, like resists<br>
<br>
3.  Summoned FT/Clarity?    Keep dreaming...   Don't get me wrong, this would be very handy.  But I can't say that I *need* it, or that mages *require* it<br>
<br>
4. Ports?  - ditto.  (if you're willing to work on faction; OT gate hammer and Thurg gate potion give you 2 &quot;ports&quot;, plus the 3 shammy gate potions)<br>
<br>
6. Pet-only SoW is ironic, but once you get Jboots, Tboots, SoW potions, or AA run speed, you only need to boost pet's speed.<br>
<br>
8.  The shield line is a self-only line that all int casters get, I think.   I doubt it's goin to be changed.  It would kinda be nice if the phantom armor was changed to allow us to buff others, so when a newbie asks for a buff, we'd have *something* useful to give them (I can DS them, but by the time he runs back to the orc camp, it's half gone).  I would like to be able to cast burnout on other's pets -- can you imagine BO on a dire charm?  (ok, they'd probably restrict it to only summoned pets - but it would help add some extra power)<br>
<br>
9.  Summoned Plate?  Sword of Runes?  I don't want to use them -- my gear is better.  I think the ones which are useful to us (summoned resist items, summoned focus items, coldstones, etc) we can use already<br>
<br>
10.  I would *love* to be able to summon more useful weapons, even if they were only used in CR situations.  Just because what we can summon now is so *useless*, except as pet weapons.  To keep it from being unbalancing, VI could make them level based, so we can't summon a too good weapon for level 1's.  But heck, they are NORENT anyways.<br>
<br>
11. Um, Elemental Armor?<br>
<br>
<br>
