<br>
Ask, but recieving is a different story. Don't forget about the myriad of other classes out there that do what you propose already. VI (while sending mixed signals) seems to promote interclass dependancy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you are content being a inzone taxi and a vending machine so be it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Frankly, I'm content to be a nice hefty damage dealer. Am I on par with rogues? No, but perhaps I aught to be for my lack of defense (a la evade). However, Balancing is still going on, and rogues are already deemed 'balanced' so soon enough we might see some evening out between us and a melee.<br>
<br>
I still feel I can do more damage, if put to task, than a rogue can, and I can do so in a shorter time period. Over the long haul, though.. then it gets funky. Those that content themselves to be taxi's or vending machines must not be all that creative with their skills.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you are content with getting really slow xp wether due to the fact that you need to kill twice as many mobs in most cases as<br>
another soloing class to get the same xp or the only groups<br>
you can get your pet gets more xp than you do so be it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It depends. Frankly, that experience thing bugged me, still bugs me, and I see no place for it in the modern day EQ. That's an argument already hashed out, though. Besides, there are workarounds, and even though VI doesn't promote working around a limitation, if they're going to put stupid restrictions in the game, then we're going to avoid them. If they don't see that, and reevaluate the &quot;fun&quot; factor of what the limitations cause (or lack thereof), then we talk to VI in other ways.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If VI can't provide<br>
the gaming experience I want and Shadowbane or another online game can I will vote with my wallet. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> While I'm not saying that Magicians could not use some kind of improvement in damage output at high end</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, VI can only provide you the tools in game to make the best gaming experience for yourself. This isn't a single player game, this is multiplayer. There are tons of other people on the game that VI does not control. They provide tools and skills to use in both downtime and uptime. They provide (try to, I think anyways) a wide range of skills per each class, or really good narrow skill set, and it's up to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to figure out how to use them.<br>
<br>
Though if you're unhappy with VI not catering to your every whim, then vote with your wallet and go find another game where they do. If you find such a place where they give you what you want all the time, and it doesn't throw things out of whack, let us all know. Some of us are capable of having fun with the skills given us, being inventive with that skillset, and providing or even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> making</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a role for ourselves that we find fun.<br>
