<br>
Are we nukers?   Are we melee?  Are we mana xfer?   Are we utility/debuffs?  Should we be porting?  Should we be casting SoW?  Summoning Clarity items?<br>
<br>
Some of the thing brought up in the thread I disagree with quite strongly (as, no doubt, many might agree).<br>
<br>
IMOHO, we don't need a SoW, for crying out loud.   Pets used to travel at the same speed as Mages, don't you know...and people complained that a soloing Mage w/Jboots or SoW potions had a lagging pet all the time (no defense, pet getting lost, etc).  So, Verant kindly adds a pet-SoW line, and now you complain why you just can't cast SoW period?   /em sigh.<br>
<br>
Ports?  C'mon, that is a Druid and Wizzy &quot;class defining&quot; ability.   There are plenty of other ways to get around without ports.  OT Hammer, Gate, Gate potions, The Nexus, Firepots, /auc WTB Port to xxxx.   Why diffuse more legitimate issues with requests for ports?  /em boggle.  Perhaps there might be some RP reason for us to port to the Plane of Sky, or if they make Elemental planes, but I won't care at all if these always go to Wizzies, as they rightfully should.<br>
<br>
Mana-regen?  All of us casters need more.  This is not a Mage-specific issue.   It is up to Verant to decide to up regen rates for us casters.  While summoning a Clarity item would be nice, I'd rather see some regen put on some FT items that are easier to get for all Wis/Int casters, or just change the mana-regen rates for meditate.<br>
<br>
What are we Mages?   We are, or should be, a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> damage-doer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> class like Wizzies and Rogues, with some extra utilities thrown in.   IMOHO we have more than enough utility AS-IS.   So, I agree with some of the posters points regarding these issues (better pets, or pet-specific weapons, better nukes, etc), but I feel it would be better to leave out some of the filler material that surely will weaken &quot;our&quot; position. <p><u>Seek Pyremaker</u><br>
Mage 54th Season, Xegony<br>
The Ring of Truth
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ud5aidan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>D5 AidaN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(4/16/02 7:05:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Things that should be coming but never will</span><hr size=1> Again, I wish VI was 10x more vocal about what they were tinkering with ingame. But I see why they're tight lipped, as half of you would expect everything they mention to go live and then be absolutely furious when it doesn't =/<br>
<br>
Pet's need an upgrade, but it's not as severe as a lot of you claim. Raiding is about their only weak point. I dunno, maybe I'm playing a different game.<br>
<br>
As for as ports go, I wouldn't mind seeing something like the teleports in UO. Around 1000mana, opens a gate that an infinite number of people can walk through, sustains itself for 1 minute. Maybe 1 to each continent. This way, no random person is going to be asking you for a port, as you will laugh in their face (unless they're offering 500pp+, which they won't). Be good to mobilize and move your guild without having druids and wizzies going back and forth grabbing everyone.<br>
<br>
I completely agree that we should have better weapon summons. Limit them to 55+ for pete's sake, but at least make them usuable instead of laughable. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34808>Aidonis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utukodo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukodo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#333333>(4/16/02 7:09:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Things that should be coming but never will</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 2 Being restored to the 2nd best blast damage dealers on all mobs and I mean all mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
